{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b244d31f-0455-406b-aeff-bf0174b67efc","content":"The template is **not quite ready** to publish. Here are the issues:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation and editor support\n- `groupIdentity` — needed for versioning/updating templates on NuGet\n- `precedence` — important when multiple versions of the template coexist\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- `description` — NuGet listing will look empty without it\n- `defaultName` — controls the default project name (e.g., `WebApi1`)\n\n**Suggestions:**\n- Add `\"preferNameDirectory\": true` for typical project template behavior\n- Consider adding a `\"baselines\"` or `\"postActions\"` section if restore is needed\n\n**Minimum fix** to be publish-ready — add at least:\n```json\n\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\",\n\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\",\n\"precedence\": 100,\n\"description\": \"A template for creating a Web API project\",\n\"defaultName\": \"WebApi1\"\n```\n\nThe structure and symbols are valid, but the metadata gaps would make it hard to discover and manage on NuGet.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"52c6b33d-8034-4e3d-9219-6c260a11d10e","outputTokens":272,"requestId":"93CB:328887:EAF4755:10103B47:69F2A8DB"},"id":"17ffa9b8-3d99-4ce5-948b-227341beb9d2","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:57:07.890Z","parentId":"a3db464a-4376-41d0-9db3-730e090b8f44"}
